review_blob: A personal favourite.750ml bottle at Den Gode Nabo in Trondheim. Near black with crisp slightly brown head. Fruity, plum/raisins, vanilla and caramel taste. Smells much the same although woodier. Well concealed alcohol taste. Try it, love it!
Golden, little to no white head. Fruity sweet with noticable alcohol. Coriander, orange, slightly yeasty. Dry finish. Great triple.
beer_name: AleSmith / Mikkeller / Stone Belgian Style Tripel Ale
